Extract Values from Raster to Points in R

Joshua Hatch

3/8/2022

First, we need to load some R libraries were going to use (if you dont have these already installed, you will need to do so before running the following code).

library(stars)
library(dplyr)
library(magrittr)
library(ggplot2)

Load loggerhead track

Im going to use an example loggerhead turtle track from the MARSS R package and convert it to an sf object.

## load example loggerhead track from MARSS R package
data(list = 'loggerhead', package = 'MARSS')

## subset to get turtle named Mary Lee
mary_lee = loggerhead %>% filter(turtle == 'MaryLee') %>% mutate(date = as.Date(paste0(year, '-', month, '-', day))) %>% st_as_sf(., coords = c('lon', 'lat'), crs = 4326)

## take a look
plot(mary_lee$geometry, axes = TRUE)

Load bathymetry

Now Im going to load the ETOPO1 Ice Surface grid-registered raster and convert it to a stars object.

## load ETOPO1 raster
etopo1 = here::here('data-raw', 'ETOPO1', 'ETOPO1_Ice_g_geotiff.tif') %>% read_stars() %>% st_set_crs(4326)

## take a look
plot(etopo1, axes = TRUE)

Extract bathymetry to loggerhead turtle track (points)

We often want to extract values from raster data. For example, the bathymetry at a location along a turtles track.

## visualize extraction
ggplot() +
  geom_stars(data = etopo1 %>% st_crop(st_bbox(mary_lee))) +
  geom_sf(data = mary_lee) +
  labs(x = NULL, y = NULL)

## extract raster values to points
mary_lee %<>% mutate(btm_depth = etopo1 %>% st_extract(., at = geometry) %>% pull(ETOPO1_Ice_g_geotiff.tif))

## plot depth over time
ggplot(data = mary_lee, aes(x = date, y = btm_depth)) + 
  geom_line(size = 1) + 
  labs(x = 'date', y = 'bottom depth (m)')
